Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Section 1: Recapitulation of sixPlaneAlpha", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fe5a7c5b-6a40-4743-8c84-ffb3ab8ae148"],

Cell["\<\
The ambient space is R^8 endowed with the SO(4,4)-invariant split-signature \
metric:

  \[Eta]88 = diag(1,1,1,1,-1,-1,-1,-1),  i.e.  <x,x> = x0^2+x1^2+x2^2+x3^2 - \
x4^2-x5^2-x6^2-x7^2.

This is the standard pseudo-Euclidean norm on R^{4,4} studied in the \
repository.

The 16-component Dirac spinor Psi = {Psi1, Psi2} is decomposed under the 8x8 \
chirality operator \[Sigma]88 = \[Gamma]88[1].\[Gamma]88[2].\[Gamma]88[3]:
  * Psi1 (Type 1, left-handed): \[Sigma]88 . Psi1 = +Psi1
  * Psi2 (Type 2, right-handed): \[Sigma]88 . Psi2 = -Psi2

Via Cartan's triality (which identifies the vector, Type-1 spinor, and Type-2 \
spinor representations of Spin(4,4)), each 8-component chiral spinor maps to \
a vector in V = R^8:
  v1 = triality(Psi1),  v2 = triality(Psi2).

Two 7-planes (hyperplanes) are defined as the orthogonal complements to these \
vectors with respect to \[Eta]88:
  H1 = { x in V : <x, v1>_\[Eta]88 = 0 }   (dimension 7)
  H2 = { x in V : <x, v2>_\[Eta]88 = 0 }   (dimension 7)

The intersection sixPlaneAlpha = H1 intersect H2 generically has dimension 8 \
- 2 = 6.

From the README: 'the 6-plane of their intersection identified; todo: \
associate 6-plane with 3 generations of Einstein-Rosen 2-planes.'

The key: 6 = 3 x 2, so sixPlaneAlpha decomposes into 3 real 2-planes, each \
one an Einstein-Rosen bridge generation.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.983596184420897*^9, 3.983596184430954*^9}, {
  3.9835966112689323`*^9, 3.9835966200570374`*^9}, {3.9835973585828342`*^9, 
  3.983597360356311*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f5158353-6731-46a4-8dae-\
ea3e9bdc800e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Section 2: Explicit Construction of sixPlaneAlpha", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5353d73a-d27f-4362-855e-d3c774399998"],

Cell["\<\
We work with the ambient R^8 and split metric \[Eta]88 = \
diag(1,1,1,1,-1,-1,-1,-1). The two 7-planes are defined by linear conditions \
on x: \[Eta]88.v1 and \[Eta]88.v2 are the normal covectors. sixPlaneAlpha = \
NullSpace of the 2x8 matrix [\[Eta]88.v1; \[Eta]88.v2]^T.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9835961844345303`*^9, 
  3.98359618444709*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0814d6ff-edb8-4705-9ed6-\
4380a273633b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"--", 
     RowBox[{"--", " ", "Symbolic"}]}], " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"construction", " ", "--"}], "--"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\n", 
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Split", " ", "metric", " ", "for", " ", 
    RowBox[{"R", "^", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"4", ",", "4"}], "}"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"eta", " ", "=", " ", 
     RowBox[{"DiagonalMatrix", "[", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "1", ",", "1", ",", "1", ",", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "*)"}], "\n", 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{"eta", "===", "\[Eta]88"}], "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Print", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<'Ambient' split metric \[Eta]88 = \>\"", ",", 
     RowBox[{"MatrixForm", "[", "\[Eta]88", "]"}]}], "]"}], ";"}]}]], "Input",\

 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9835959697405643`*^9, 3.983596006592903*^9}, {
  3.983596135858692*^9, 3.9835961444173803`*^9}, {3.9835964654140778`*^9, 
